page.title: 11Smuggling at Nanjizel.
page.content: Smuggling at Nanjizel. It was night we were smuggling fifty crates of champayne. We had a big boat and four small boats. The little boats would take ten crates of champayne each. When we got near the shore we stopped our engines and got our little boats out and loaded them with champayne then we got to shore. We were looking out for police and coastguards. The shore was rocky. And there was lots of sea weed. One of the boats went back to get the other ten crates. Then we heard shouting, the police and the customs men were coming! We all scrambled in the little boats and rowed back to our large boat. The police were shooting at us but we escaped because the cliff got in their way. It was a lucky escape this time!
